**Summary of extracted program graphs from `BaseAuction.sol`:**

- **SG-001 checkUpkeep**: View function that iterates allowlisted assets, identifies eligible auctions to start (sufficient USD value) and ended auctions (duration elapsed or dust balance). Gates all new auctions on valid assetOut price (INV-002).

- **SG-002 performUpkeep**: Worker-role-gated function that pulls funds from feeAggregator, starts new auctions (setting `s_auctionStarts[asset] = block.timestamp`), and ends completed auctions (returning residual to feeAggregator). Special handling for assetOut itself (forward to receiver, INV-005).

- **SG-003 bid**: Core auction participation with manual reentrancy guard (`s_entered`). Validates auction liveness, minimum bid USD value, and available balance. Transfers asset to bidder BEFORE pulling payment (callback pattern, INV-007), enabling flash-loan-style bids via `auctionCallback`.

- **SG-004 _applyAssetParamsUpdates**: Admin function to add/remove asset parameters. Validates no live auction conflict, allowlist membership, decimal match, and price multiplier bounds. AssetOut skips duration/multiplier validation (INV-010).

- **SG-005 _setAssetOut**: Changes the payment token. Requires no live auctions, deletes old assetOut params on change (INV-013).

- **SG-006 _setFeeAggregator**: Sets fee aggregator with ERC165 interface check. Self-reference (`address(this)`) bypasses the check for standalone mode (INV-014).

- **SG-007 _getAssetOutAmount**: Pure price computation with linear decay from `startingPriceMultiplier` to `endingPriceMultiplier`. All rounding is UP (mulDivUp, mulWadUp) favoring the protocol (INV-016, INV-017).

